studyInterventions.name: Tele-exergaming Exercise Intervention
studyInterventions.description: Remote in-home exercise system for adults with mild cognitive impairment or mild dementia designed to improve balance and cognition during distractive conditioning while remotely supervised via telemedicine interface

studyInterventions.name: Supervised Exercise Intervention
studyInterventions.description: Exercise intervention performed in a supervised condition (control group in Phase II RCT)

interventions.name: Tele-exergaming Exercise Intervention
interventions.description: Remote in-home exercise system for adults with mild cognitive impairment or mild dementia designed to improve balance and cognition during distractive conditioning while remotely supervised via telemedicine interface

interventions.name: Supervised Exercise Intervention
interventions.description: Exercise intervention performed in a supervised condition (control group in Phase II RCT)

devices.name: LegSys
devices.purpose: Validated body worn sensors for gait assessment using five sensor modules attached to right and left anterior shins, right and left anterior thighs, and posteriorly to the lower back to estimate spatio-temporal gait parameters

devices.name: BalanSens
devices.purpose: Validated body worn sensors for balance assessment measuring ankle and hip motion in three dimensions, 2D COM sway, and RCI in ML and AP directions

devices.name: PAMSys
devices.purpose: Wearable device for physical activity monitoring measuring number of steps, duration of sitting, standing, walking and lying, time and number of sit-to-stand transitions, and walking speed for 48 hours

devices.name: Exergaming Platform
devices.purpose: In-home exercise system with ankle reaching tasks and motor-cognitive exercises including interactive Trail-Making test (iTMT) for remote exercise intervention
